Insights¶

Sales Insights¶

1.Sales Seasonality:¶

  • January and February are consistently the lowest-performing months in terms of sales.
  • September and November emerge as peak sales months, indicating strong seasonal or promotional demand.
  • Quarter 4 (October to December) contributes the highest overall sales, making it crucial for revenue planning.

2. Segment-Wise Performance:¶

  • The Consumer segment generates the majority of sales, showcasing strong B2C performance. This is followed by the Corporate and Home Office segments, which also show consistent contributions.

3. Category-Wise Sales:¶

  • Technology is the top-selling category, driven by high demand for electronics. Furniture ranks second, followed closely by Office Supplies.

4. Sub-Categories by Sales:¶

  • Chairs (Furniture), Phones (Technology), and Storage (Office Supplies) are the leading sub-categories in total sales value. These sub-categories should be prioritized in inventory planning and promotional strategies.

Profit Insights¶

The store has demonstrated consistent yearly growth in profit, indicating a healthy business trajectory.

1. Category-Wise Profit¶

  • Technology has highest profit followed by Office Supplies and Furniture. When evaluated on Sales to Profit Ratio:
  • Office Supplies show the highest efficiency with a 15% profit margin. Technology follows with 13%, and Furniture trails with just 4%.

2. Sub-Category Performance¶

  • Technology Top-performing subcateogry: Copiers followed by Phones, and Accessories.
  • Office Supplies Top-performing subcateogry: Paper followed by Binders and Storage.
  • Furniture Top-performing subcateogry : Chairs and Furnishings are the most profitable.

3. Loss-Making Sub-Categories¶

  • Tables and Bookcases (under Furniture), and Supplies (Office Supplies) often negative profits despite high sales volumes.

State-wise Summary¶

  • California has the highest sales, followed by New York, Texas, Washington, Pennsylvania, Florida, Illinois, Ohio, Michigan, and Virginia.
  • Even Though Texas, Pennsylvania, Florida, Illinois, and Ohio have high sales but are losing money.

City-wise Summary¶

  • New York City has the best sales and profits followed by Los Angeles, Seattle,

San Francisco, Philadelphia, Houston, Chicago, San Diego, Jacksonville, and Springfield.
